<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="utf-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1">
  <title>Twitch Bible Bot</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body>
  <main class="container">
    <section class="hero card">
      <h1>Twitch Bible Bot</h1>
      <p>Twitch bot for Bible verses. Streamers can connect their Twitch account, enable the bot for their channel, and choose a default translation.</p>
      <div class="actions">
        <% if (user) { %>
          <a class="button" href="/dashboard">Open dashboard</a>
        <% } else { %>
          <a class="button" href="/auth/twitch">Connect with Twitch</a>
        <% } %>
      </div>
    </section>
    <section class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h2>How it works</h2>
        <p>After a streamer connects with Twitch, the bot stores their channel and joins it automatically. Viewers can then type references like <code>John 3:16</code> or <code>Psalms 23:1 WEB</code>.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Translations</h2>
        <p>The bot supports friendly Bible translation aliases like<b> ESV, KJV, NKJV, KJVA, ASV, ABT, AAB, BSB, BBE, DARBY, DRA, EMTV, JPS, LSV, LXX, F35, FBV, GLV, GNV, WEB, WEBC, WEBPB, WEBU, WMB, YLT, NET, OJB, T4T, ULB</b>, and more, all mapped to Bible translation IDs.</p>
      </article>
    </section>
    
    <section class="grid">
      <article class="card">
        <h2>Support me!</h2>
        <p>Running and maintaining these services isn’t just expensive—it’s something I’ve been consistently investing my time, energy, and personal resources into to keep everything alive and working smoothly. It’s an ongoing commitment that means a lot to me, and any support genuinely makes a difference and helps me continue keeping it all running.</p>
        <a href="https://www.paypal.com/donate/?hosted_button_id=JEEJTQ2G6BBUL" target="_blank"><img src="https://elcast.org/donate.png" height="64"></a>
      </article>
    </section>
    
  </main>
</body>
</html>